From: conda-forge
Subject: [PATCH] Fix C++20 aggregate initialization of Vertex, HistoInfo and NumDenPair

ROOT 6.40 propagates cxx_std_20 via its INTERFACE compile features, which
raises Hammer's requested cxx_std_17 to C++20 for the whole build. Under
C++20 (P1008R1) a class with any user-declared constructor - including a
defaulted one declared in-class - is no longer an aggregate, so the
member-wise brace initialization of these structs stops compiling with
"no matching constructor". Dropping the redundant defaulted default
constructor restores aggregate status; the implicit default constructor is
still generated, so default construction keeps working.
---
--- a/include/Hammer/Math/MultiDim/Ops/DotOuterOptimizer.hh
+++ b/include/Hammer/Math/MultiDim/Ops/DotOuterOptimizer.hh
@@ -58,8 +58,6 @@
 
         struct Vertex {
             enum class Type : std::uint8_t { LEFT, RIGHT, COLLAPSED, UNUSED };
-
-            Vertex() = default;
 
             Type _type;
             VertexId _outerPosition;
--- a/include/Hammer/Tools/IOTypes.hh
+++ b/include/Hammer/Tools/IOTypes.hh
@@ -145,8 +145,6 @@
 
     struct HistoInfo {
 
-        HistoInfo() = default;
-
         std::string name;
         std::string scheme;
         std::string specialization;
--- a/include/Hammer/IndexTypes.hh
+++ b/include/Hammer/IndexTypes.hh
@@ -152,8 +152,6 @@
     template <typename T>
     struct NumDenPair {
 
-        NumDenPair() = default;
-
         T numerator;
         T denominator;
 
